\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 7. L. chloroticum} A. Kerner & Murb., {\i Lunds Univ. Årsskr.}{\b  27}: 109 (1891) ({\i L. graminifolium} auct. balcan., non (L.) Lam.). Stems 20-35 cm, simple or with 2-3 branches. Basal leaves narrowly cuneate, long-petiolate, with 3-7 teeth at apex; lower cauline leaves entire below; middle cauline leaves 1-3 mm wide, shortly petiolate or sessile, remotely toothed, the teeth acute, erect. Capitula 3-5 cm in diameter; involucral bracts usually pale green, with a pale, scarious margin.{\i  Grassland and pastures up to} 1800 {\i m. • W. & C. Jugoslavia.} Ju.
