\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 8. L. corsicum} (Less.) DC., {\i Prodr.}{\b  6}: 47 (1838). Stems 20-60 cm, usually simple, somewhat pubescent. Basal and lower cauline leaves lobed to pinnatipartite; middle cauline leaves pinnatilobed to 2-pinnatisect, with ovate to linear, mucronate to aristate segments. Capitula 2-3 cm in diameter; involucral bracts with a brownish-black margin. Pappus of ligulate florets a corona at least ½ as long as the corolla-tube. 2n = 36.{\i  Rocks and rocky slopes. • Corse. }Co.
